==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[maki|māki]], Old Norse [[mækir]], Gothic [[𐌼𐌴𐌺𐌹]] (borrowed into Slavic: see e.g. Russian [[меч]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'me:ʧe/

===Noun===
'''mēċe''' ''m''
# ''(Poetic)'' a kind of [[sword]]
#:''Flodweard gesloh unhleowan wæg alde mece'': the flood-guardian struck the unprotective wave with an ancient sword.  (''Exodus'')

